## Vaccine Effectiveness Examples

| Vaccine Type           | Typical Effectiveness Range | Notes                                                                                 |
|-----------------------|-----------------------------|---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| Measles               | ~99%                        | One of the most effective vaccines; requires high coverage for herd immunity          |
| Influenza (Flu)       | 20% - 60%                   | Varies annually due to virus mutation and vaccine strain match                         |
| COVID-19 (Pfizer/Moderna) | 90% - 95% (efficacy)         | Real-world effectiveness can decline over time and with new variants                   |
| COVID-19 (Johnson & Johnson) | ~66% (efficacy)               | Lower efficacy than mRNA vaccines, tested later during variant circulation              |
| Whooping Cough (Pertussis) | 80% initially, drops to 60% over 4 years | Booster doses required due to waning immunity                                         |

*Source: [Mandal, 2022](https://www.news-medical.net/health/Vaccine-Effectiveness.aspx), [Ellis, 2020](https://www.dailymail.co.uk/health/article-8956485/Why-no-vaccine-100-effective-Wide-variation-populations-immune-systems.html)*

